position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2009,\"repo\":\"hashicorp/terraform-cdk\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - CDK (Cloud Development Kit) for Terraform allows developers to use familiar programming languages to define cloud infrastructure and provision it through HashiCorp Terraform.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T22:48:46.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"shuaibiyy/awesome-terraform","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l5k1ai_GBDE\">Terraform explained in 15 mins</a> - Terraform explained in 15 mins.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T22:37:37.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"shuaibiyy/awesome-terraform","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SLB_c_ayRMo\">Terraform Course</a> - Automate your AWS cloud infrastructure.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T22:37:37.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"shuaibiyy/awesome-terraform","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LVgP63BkhKQ\">How to Build Reusable, Composable, Battle tested Terraform Modules</a> - Yevgeniy Brikman talks about how to write Terraform code so that it is reusable, composable and testable. The presentation focuses on Terraform modules, but also provides a brief and clear explanation of what problem Terraform was created to solve and a short demo of Terraform basics (~39 min, October 2017).</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T22:37:37.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"EbookFoundation/free-programming-books","categoryHTML":"<h3>SQL (implementation agnostic)</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/bobbyiliev/introduction-to-sql\">Introduction to SQL</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/bobbyiliev/introduction-to-sql\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">66</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":66,\"repo\":\"bobbyiliev/introduction-to-sql\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Bobby Iliev (Markdown, PDF)</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T21:27:59.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Online Community</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>The #clschool, #lisp, #ccl, #sbcl and <a href=\"https://www.cliki.net/IRC\">other rooms</a> on the <a href=\"https://libera.chat/\">Libera.Chat</a> network are great places for learning about Common Lisp. (<a href=\"https://gist.github.com/joepie91/df80d8d36cd9d1bde46ba018af497409\">Freenode should be avoided.</a>)</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T20:46:08.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"DanailMinchev/awesome-eosio","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2><h4>Desktop</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://greymass.com/en/anchor/\">Anchor Wallet</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/greymass/anchor\">greymass/anchor</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/greymass/anchor\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">397</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":397,\"repo\":\"greymass/anchor\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Official GitHub.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T19:41:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit","categoryHTML":"<h4>Native Apps (closed source)</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ualabee.com/company/\">Ualabee</a> - Community driven trip planner with focus on user interaction, users can report anomalies, upload pictures, edit transit data and chat with other passengers.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T17:44:14.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ciconia/awesome-music","categoryHTML":"<h2>Music Programming</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://py-modular.readthedocs.io/\">py-modular</a> - a modular and experimental programming environment with basic DSP routines in python.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T16:45:41.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"lauris/awesome-scala","categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://leanpub.com/pfhais\">Pure functional HTTP APIs in Scala</a> by Jens Grassel</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T13:00:43.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Public Data Resources</h2><h3>Demographic</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/acs\">American Community Survey (ACS)</a> - The American Community Survey (ACS) helps local officials, community leaders, and businesses understand the changes taking place in their communities. It is the premier source for detailed population and housing information for the United States. Additional Information: <a href=\"https://www.census.gov/geographies/mapping-files/time-series/geo/tiger-data.html\">Geodata Download</a>/<a href=\"https://data.census.gov/cedsci/\">Table Data Access</a></li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Public Data Resources</h2><h3>Demographic</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.nhgis.org/\">IPUMS National Historic GIS</a> - The National Historical Geographic Information System (NHGIS) provides easy access to summary tables and time series of population, housing, agriculture, and economic data, along with GIS-compatible boundary files, for years from 1790 through the present and for all levels of U.S. census geography, including states, counties, tracts, and blocks.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Public Data Resources</h2><h3>Employment</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://lehd.ces.census.gov/\">Longitudinal Employer-Household Dynamics (LEHD)</a> -  The LEHD program combines these administrative data, additional administrative data and data from censuses and surveys. From these data, the program creates statistics on employment, earnings, and job flows at detailed levels of geography and industry and for different demographic groups. Additional Information:<a href=\"https://onthemap.ces.census.gov/\">On The Map Download Page</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Public Data Resources</h2><h3>Environment and Ecosystem Services</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.epa.gov/enviroatlas\">EnviroAtlas</a> - EnviroAtlas is a collection of interactive tools and resources that allows users to explore the many benefits people receive from nature, often referred to as ecosystem services within the United States.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Public Data Resources</h2><h3>Environment and Ecosystem Services</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.usgs.gov/core-science-systems/ngp/national-hydrography/access-national-hydrography-products\">National Hydrography</a> - The NHDPlus High Resolution (NHDPlus HR), National Hydrography Dataset (NHD), and Watershed Boundary Dataset (WBD) are available for download and as map services. These datasets can help inform environmental planning and storm water management efforts in the US.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Public Data Resources</h2><h3>Health</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.countyhealthrankings.org/\">County Health Rankings</a> - The annual Rankings provide a revealing snapshot of how health is influenced by where we live, learn, work, and play.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Public Data Resources</h2><h3>Resilience and Natural Hazards</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://coast.noaa.gov/slr/\">Sea Level Rise Viewer</a> - NOAA provided map viewer is to provide federal, state, and local coastal resource managers and planners with a preliminary look at sea level rise and coastal flooding impacts.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Public Data Resources</h2><h3>Transportation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://data-usdot.opendata.arcgis.com/\">BTS Open Data Site</a> - On the BTS Open Data site, browse geospatial data that is part of the BTS National Transportation Atlas Database (NTAD) product. NTAD is a set of nationwide (United States) geographic databases of public spatial information for transportation facilities and networks; flows of people, goods, vehicles, and craft over the transportation networks; and social, economic, and environmental conditions that affect or are affected by the transportation networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Public Data Resources</h2><h3>Transportation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://transit.land\">Transitland</a> - Transitland is an open data platform that collects GTFS, GTFS Realtime, and other open data feeds from over 2,500 transit operators in over 55 countries. Additional Information: <a href=\"https://www.interline.io/\">Interline</a>,<a href=\"https://github.com/transitland\">GitHub</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Public Data Resources</h2><h3>Transportation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.bts.gov/geospatial/national-transportation-noise-map\">National Noise Map</a> - Data within the National Transportation Noise Map represent potential noise levels across the nation for an average annual day for the specified year.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Public Data Resources</h2><h3>Transportation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://geoffboeing.com/publications/street-network-models-indicators-world/\">Global Urban Street Networks</a> - Ready‐to‐use global street network models and calculated indicators in a GIS format. Additional Information:<a href=\"https://dataverse.harvard.edu/dataset.xhtml?persistentId=doi:10.7910/DVN/E5TPDQ\">Geopackage Download</a></li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Vendor Data Resources</h2><h3>Demographic</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.esri.com/en-us/arcgis/products/tapestry-segmentation/zip-lookup\">Esri Tapestry Segmentation</a> - Provides concise information on the demographic, economic, education and consumer characteristics of populations based on ZIP code.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Vendor Data Resources</h2><h3>Land Use</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.corelogic.com/\">CoreLogic</a> - Provides high quality parcel data, providing instant access to detailed property characteristics, sales records, valuation and digital copies of current county assessor documents.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Data Specifications</h2><h3>Transportation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.sharedstreets.io\">SharedStreets</a> - SharedStreets Referencing System is a global, non-proprietary linear referencing system for describing streets maintained by SharedStreets. Additional Information: <a href=\"https://github.com/sharedstreets/sharedstreets-ref-system\">GitHub</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sharedstreets/sharedstreets-ref-system\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">164</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":164,\"repo\":\"sharedstreets/sharedstreets-ref-system\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--></li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Data Specifications</h2><h3>Transportation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.curblr.org\">CurbLR</a> -  An open data specification for curb regulations maintained by SharedStreets. Additional Information: <a href=\"https://www.github.com/sharedstreets/curblr\">GitHub</a>, Demo: interactive <a href=\"https://demo.curblr.org/\">map and example feed</a>, Blog post: <a href=\"https://medium.com/sharedstreets/crossroads-for-the-curb-be3137154148\">Why CurbLR was built</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Data Specifications</h2><h3>Transportation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs\">GTFS</a> - The General Transit Feed Specification is a popular standard for describing transit systems.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Data Specifications</h2><h3>Transportation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/d-wasserman/shared-row\">shared-row</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/d-wasserman/shared-row\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">9</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":9,\"repo\":\"d-wasserman/shared-row\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A data specification for representing street right of ways.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Data Specifications</h2><h3>Transportation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/NABSA/gbfs\">GBFS</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/NABSA/gbfs\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">521</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":521,\"repo\":\"NABSA/gbfs\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - The General Bikeshare Feed Specification is a standardized data feed for shared mobility system availability.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Data Specifications</h2><h3>Transportation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/openmobilityfoundation/mobility-data-specification\">MDS</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/openmobilityfoundation/mobility-data-specification\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">510</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":510,\"repo\":\"openmobilityfoundation/mobility-data-specification\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - The Mobility Data Specification is a data standard to enable communication between mobility companies and local governments.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Data Specifications</h2><h3>Transportation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vta/Managed-and-Tolled-Lanes-Feed-Specification\">MTLFS</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vta/Managed-and-Tolled-Lanes-Feed-Specification\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">8</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":8,\"repo\":\"vta/Managed-and-Tolled-Lanes-Feed-Specification\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - The Managed and Tolled Lanes Feed Specification is intended to be used by the managed lanes and toll industry for the standardization and sharing of dynamic toll rates, and any managed lane purpose including but not limited to, ramp metering, bus only lanes, express lanes, especially if the resources are being priced dynamically.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://pandas.pydata.org/\">Pandas</a> - Flexible and powerful data analysis / manipulation library for Python, providing labeled data structures similar to R data.frame objects, statistical functions, and much more.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://pro.arcgis.com/en/pro-app/latest/arcpy/get-started/what-is-arcpy-.htm\">Arcpy</a> - ArcPy is a Python site package that provides a useful and productive way to perform geographic data analysis, data conversion, data management, and map automation with Python.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developers.arcgis.com/python/api-reference/\">ArcGIS Python API</a> - The ArcGIS API for Python is a powerful, modern and easy to use Pythonic library to perform GIS visualization and analysis, spatial data management and GIS system administration tasks that can run both interactively, and using scripts. This library enables easy use of pandas within the ArcGIS platform.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://udst.github.io/pandana/\">Pandana</a> - Urban network analysis library intended to help planners compute quick accessibility metrics or shortest paths. Additional Information: License: AGPL-3.0 License: Provider: UrbanSim Inc. (UDST).</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><