this sort of information.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://shiny.rstudio.com/\">R Shiny</a> - Create dynamic, web-friendly visualizations of data using R. Additional Information: <a href=\"https://shiny.rstudio.com/tutorial/\">Shiny Tutorial</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/sf/index.html\">simplefeatures(sf)</a> - Support for simple features, a standardized way to encode spatial vector data in R.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/\">ggplot2</a> - Resource for plotting a wide range of data (useful for visualizing survey data). Additional Information: GNU GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/tidytext/vignettes/tidytext.html\">tidytext</a> - Go-to library for text mining--often used in tandem with ggplot or other text mining libraries.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Platforms and Software Resources</h2><h3>Geospatial Data and Visualization</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.esri.com/en-us/arcgis/about-arcgis/overview\">ArcGIS</a> - This platform is a geographic information system (GIS) for working with maps and geographic information maintained by the Environmental Systems Research Institute (Esri).</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Platforms and Software Resources</h2><h3>Geospatial Data and Visualization</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://kepler.gl/\">kepler.gl</a> - Kepler is a data agnostic, WebGL empowered, high-performance web application for geospatial analytic visualizations. Additional Information: <a href=\"https://docs.kepler.gl/docs/api-reference\">API Reference</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Platforms and Software Resources</h2><h3>Urban Planning Tools and Platforms</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://urbanfootprint.com/\">UrbanFootPrint</a> - Web-based planning tool serving curated urban, environmental, and economic data to urban practitioners and equipping them with the analytic capabilities to plan and improve communities faster, better, and at lower cost.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Platforms and Software Resources</h2><h3>Urban Planning Tools and Platforms</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.remix.com/\">Remix</a> - A platform to empower cities to plan the best possible transportation system — from public transit to safer streets to ever-increasing new modes of mobility. Remix provides tools to edit &#x26; test GTFS, generate multimodal streets, and explore relevant data.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-19T05:51:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Resources</h2><h3>Other Technology Resource Aggregators</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/CUTR-at-USF/awesome-transit\"